                    <p>Shrek searches for Fiona's cousin Artie to avoid becoming king and learns about parenthood.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card-content">
                    <p>Just what the franchise needed: a coming-of-age tale about responsibility starring a reluctant ogre. Clearly, there was no better way to milk the franchise than to throw in a whiny teenager and a midlife crisis. The jokes are as fresh as a week-old swamp, and the moral lessons? About as subtle as a club to the head.
                    </p>
